<br>
If you think see hidden sucks, imagine  watching an archer walk towards you, pull his bow and hit you for 600+ while hidden :) You only get it for 1 minute every 30 but when that happens theres litterally nothing we can do (again, if we are also solo).<br>
<br>
This change forces grouping which I think is a good thing. OK, Ill admit it, sticking solo archers is fun too :)  <p><center><br>"I am still learning" <br>
- Michelangelo</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 1:08:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't think archers have it that bad</span><hr size=1> **Edit because the board lost half of my post<br>
<br>
Sorry, Aurelius, but I have to call BS.  Archers in tight RvR groups suck just as much as they did in tight PvE groups, for the same reasons.  Watch what they actually do sometime.  They get one bow shot off before the actual combat commences (that shot fails more often in RvR than it did in PvE), then end up in melee because the game won't let them shoot at melees, but melees sure love them.  Since they didn't spec to be melee-fighters, they suck in melee.  Sure, they can still shoot at casters, but they are considered just as soft as casters as far as easy RPs go.  Let's face it, Mythic designed them extremely poorly as far as close-in fighting goes, which is what they end up being forced into.  The revenge mindset rampant right now doesn't allow archers to fall back like casters (not that casters last long either <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ).  <br>
<br>
Don't get me wrong, I don't long for the days when archers were demi-gods of the battlefield.  They needed to be brought down to mortal level.  Mythic said they'd fixed them on several occasions.  Each time, they missed the mark because they ignored what seemed obvious to everyone in the community, that full spec stealth plus range was too much(Side note: Mythic is doing the same thing to Smite Clerics.  Community complains of the CC abilities, so Mythic nerfs smite.  Go figure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rolleyes --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eyes.gif ALT=":rolleyes"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  That's for another forum, though).  Mythic finally addresses archer stealth and removes its effectiveness for archers without giving them their spec points back.  Right now, archers have almost all of the weakness of robe casters, without the advantages.<br>
<br>
Maybe when the vaporware respec goes in, archers will stop complaining so much.  They'll be able to remove all points from stealth, just as the new minstrels are doing, and spec enough melee to last more than two hits.  As far as Scouts complaining that they can no longer scout, I have no answer short of ripping out SH and going with another solution.  I've always favored limiting archers to half, or one-third, spec in stealth and making Detect Hidden more powerful.<br>
<br>
I've played a robe, an archer, a minstrel, and a couple of assassins.  I like to think my experience is balanced enough to look for class balance, instead of the revenge-seeking I see rampant in the areas of the community.  Let's not let our glee at being able to gut archers now blind us to class balance.  If we do, then we're no better than Mythic and their ham-handed attempts at balance. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/13/02 3:31:56 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uadman2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adman 2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 1:13:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't think archers have it that bad</span><hr size=1> Um couple things. <br>
<br>
We made archers to solo. If we wanted to group we'd have rolled another class. It's not fair to totally alter our playstyle this many months in.<br>
<br>
Play a hunter in a group sometime. We're worthless. We can't scout. We can't get a shot off before the tanks in the group kill the enemy. We have lousy defense. Worthless pets. No group buffs.<br>
<br>
And when I'm by myself and I pop truesight and see an assasin, I crit him and get a second shot before he closes and I still get pounded to death.<br>
<br>
Hunters, who already were lame due to taking the biggest brunt of the damage nerfs, are now nearly worthless and hardly enjoyable to play.<br>
<br>
Most would agree, just get rid of see hidden and truesight... and make detect hidden the skill it should have been. <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/seeksig3.jpg>
