<br>
Most archers I know have a reasonable spec in blades because of the assassin threat.  They have something like 30 in blades  +items which makes them deadly against leather.<br>
<br>
I personally think Hunters are cool because they have lots of options in combat.  If I rolled an archer, I would choose a Hunter.  However at this point, I think I would spec lower in stealth than people have in the past because it is now more valuable to have good melee than be invisible for an archer.<br>
<br>
I do think the beastmaster line needs some work to make it more attractive.  In concept it is cool but apparently in practice it is unpopular.<br>
