 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/13/02 3:20:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't think archers have it that bad</span><hr size=1> Lakeb,<br>
<br>
You've obviously never played an archer.  If an archer tries to fire at a target that is meleeing, they receive a message to the effect of &quot;You can't get a clear shot!&quot; over and over again (they receive this about 90% of the time).  Once that target is out of melee, the archer can fire freely.  If you've been around for awhile, you should remember the archers complaining sometime back that tanks were keeping melee-mode on all the time when traveling, thus preventing archers from shooting them.  This is yet another reason why casters are primary targets of archers.  Casters can't be in melee mode if they want to cast.  Combine that with casters' paper armor and you have easy pickings for an archer.<br>
<br>
As for archers having a good melee spec, that may be true for new archers rolling up now.  What about the established archers, though?  They don't the option right now of speccing high melee.  Their points are spent.  If Mythic ever puts in the respec, that can change.  Right now, it can't.<br>
<br>
The question about Hunters was their evade level.  It's Evade I.  Even a lot of the archer-haters admit that hunters are fairly gimped right now.  Light armor, pitiful chance to evade, short range for bows, low chance to find a pet, and it'll be grey if you find one, and a spell line that is pitiful.  All archers are hurting, but Hunters are the beaten red-headed stepchild of archers.<br>
<br>
R6 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/13/02 3:25:52 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ubernardrazorleaf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bernard Razorleaf</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.earthlink.net/~eddytaylor/data/leaves.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/02 4:18:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~eddytaylor/data/deadbernie.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I don't think archers have it that bad</span><hr size=1> The &quot;can't get a clear shot&quot; thing happens when you try to use critical shot on a target that's in melee. Tap your critical shot button again, it'll switch to a regular shot and you can shoot.<br>
<br>
We all agree: Hunters are gimped. Sorry <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  edit:</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> Yes, you can shoot things in melee, just not with a critical shot. That's why a while back they toned down archer's PvE bow aggro a LOT, because before the mob would be half dead and when you'd pop it with an arrow it would come STRAIT for you. Now, unless you pull, it's a harder to get aggro off of anyone with arrows. Really glad they made that reduction. I don't really like to stand in a group and shoot things with my bow though, it wastes waaaay too many arrows. Plus my melee is good and it's easier to take aggro off the healer with my swords. <p><BR>
