 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lakeb>Lakeb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/02 8:09:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> wow</span><hr size=1> You're right, I have never played an archer class.  I have just been on the business end of their arrows.<br>
<br>
I do think it is lame that you can't shoot someone in Melee, that sounds like a bug.  I could see Melee increasing chance to block, but not eliminating your ability to see them.  :P<br>
<br>
Why is it that hunters have lame pets again?  Is it that there are no monsters that are worth 'mastering' or is it that your spell won't permit getting a good one.  I recently rolled a mentallist and I can get yellow con mobs and hold them till my mana runs out... how does this compare to beastmaster? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/02 2:57:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: wow</span><hr size=1> Pet level is capped at 85% of your level.  At low levels, a Hunter can get up to a blue pet.  By level 20, you can only charm greens.  By the time a Hunter is ready for full RvR in the frontier (lvl 40+), I'm told that all pets are grey.  I never got that high, so I can't say from personal experience (my Hunter went inactive sometime ago).  On top of that, pets of the proper level are scarce in the frontier.  This is assuming that you go full-spec Beastcraft.  If you don't, then your pets may conn lower sooner, as the spells are capped in level mob that can be charmed, and have to be replaced with higher spells.<br>
<br>
I seem to remember a post where the devs admitted that pets are meant to be merely fluff when it comes to RvR.  Can't find the reference. <p><br>Cithar: Minstrel, MLF<br>Tyra Morsacchias: Theurgist, Nimue<br>Mortifer: Infiltrator, Nimue<br>Blageir Skytjuson: Hunter, Kay<br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uromeosix.showPublicProfile?language=EN>RomeoSix</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalWhite.gif" BORDER=0> at: 6/14/02 3:00:01 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/ulupas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lupas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/14/02 3:37:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instead of nerfing see hidden..</span><hr size=1> Some things about Hunters-<br>
<br>
Hunters get Evade 1 while Scouts and Rangers get Evade 3. Mythic has said this is an &quot;oversight&quot; from beta when Hunters had Evade 1 and Chain Armor. The armor was dropped to studded and evade was never increased.<br>
<br>
Hunters pets are 80% or 85% of their level, I forget which. The highest level pet a 50th hunter can have is level 41 or green. These are few and far between, the pets are usually gray.  Pet agro on finding stealthers is extremely low and the couple commands for pets do not work well at all. Matt Firor has stated that pets for hunters were just a &quot;novelty' so things won't get better.<br>
<br>
Hunters bow damage is the worst of the archer classes.  While Scouts and Rangers can get the fast bows of Hunters to shoot fast Hunters can not have the slow speed bows that the other Archers have so the damage is lower by a decent margin.<br>
<br>
Hunter Melee- Where to start? Hunters are the worst melee Archer class by a decent margin. The Hunter and Ranger TL and various Hunters and Rangers tested melee between the 2 classes and rangers with low weapon spec and low CD spec can out melee Hunters who use spear and have a high melee spec.  Spear has decent front loaded damage on the first hit if there is no delay but is way too slow to compete with Assassins, Ranger CD and Scout Shield Slams then Crits.<br>
<br>
So basically you end up with a class that has the worst defensive abilities (only slightly better then cloth casters vs other Archer and Melee classes), Worst melee abilities, and poorest Bow damamge of the 3 Archers.<br>
<br>
Hunters can be fun to play, even being repeatedly ganked by gray assassins who see through stealth and lead groups to kill them. But, compared to the other Archer classes and melee classes are pretty bad off.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uubergnome563.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ubergnome563</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 1:18:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instead of nerfing see hidden..</span><hr size=1> The highest ranking archer on my server (who is also the #1 rp holder on my server) has approximately 5 spec in stealth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uadman2.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Adman 2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 11:26:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instead of nerfing see hidden..</span><hr size=1> Yeah mythic looks at pets as just a &quot;fun&quot; thing, yet for a while people pointed to pets as the thing that makes up for hunters lack of bow damage.<br>
<br>
Pets, even grey ones, are extremely useful if you play them right. I've taken down red casters by throwing a grey pet on them first.<br>
<br>
But pets are a pain to deal with because they're hard to find. At 48 I can find blue pets, it's just very very rare. I can find green ones fairly easily.<br>
<br>
Pets were supposed to be what made up for our low bow damage, but you don't see too many hunters using them due to the various reasons such as the fact that if a guard patrol finds your pet, they make a beeline for you no matter how far away you are. Things that need to happen to hunter:<br>
<br>
Evade 3... NOW!<br>
<br>
Access to higher damage bows: Scouts and Rangers not only have higher delay bows, they have Mastery of Archery, which speeds up their bow draw times to near-hunter speeds.<br>
<br>
Summonable pets: that are at LEAST yellow con to us.<br>
<br>
A group buff added to our Beastcraft line: nothing uber, just something to make a group desire a hunter in PvE and RvR<br>
<br>
I call for thse 4 changes, as well as the elimination of See Hidden and Truesight. It was a lot more fun before 1.50 - Assasins owned me just fine with Detect Hidden.... now they just farm free RPs from me. <p><img src=http://members.aol.com/nycdamian/seeksig3.jpg>
<BR><BR>
"Getting better at my craft, dropping gimps, I never miss! Nay a taunting or a laugh, as you lay there sucking grass... Just a kiss, before you pass."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uashtonyew.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ashton Yew</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 12:24:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Instead of nerfing see hidden..  </span><hr size=1> Here is how I view see hidden.<br>
<br>
This is a skill that is TOO POWERFUL!!!!!!!!! It only costs 8 points where true sight is 10 points. It is a passive skill where true sight is an active skill with a 1 minute duration and a 30 minute recycle time. And level makes NO DIFFERENCE any longer for detection. <br>
<br>
Normal detection by an assassin or other player is based on level and stealth differences. I haven't played with it much to determine exact ranges, but it does make sense that if a lower level character with low stealth is more likely to be seen by an even level character with maxed stealth or a higher level character. I am more likely to get ganked by an assassin before I get it from another archer, happens to me ALL the time. And detect hidden does work, kinda anyway.<br>
<br>
Now with see hidden, you can get an assassin to L1 R8 by whatever means, and now that assassin, no matter what his level is, and see every archer and minstrel out there.<br>
<br>
Personally, I feel that one of two things should happen. <br>
<br>
1) Remove both true sight and see hidden in their entirety. (my personal choice)<br>
<br>
2) Modify see hidden such that it has some function with stealth skill. Such as increasing detection range or reducing effective stealth skill within a certain range.<br>
<br>
Just my thought and opinions on this. <br>
<br>
Flame if you will, but you won't change my mind on this.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/utanglebones00.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tanglebones00</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/15/02 11:58:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Instead of nerfing see hidden..  </span><hr size=1>  See hidden is WAY too powerful. Also anyone that doesn't think archers are hurtin is nuts <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showPrevMessage?topicID=3538.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showNextMessage?topicID=3538.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3538.topic&index=17><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.emailToFriend?topicID=3538.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.threadControl?topicID=3538.topic><img src=http://216.40.211.42/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=